{"questionId":"6029","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A wheel of mass 0.25 kg consists of a cylinder mounted on a central shaft. The shaft has a&nbsp;radius of 1.2 cm and the cylinder has a radius of 4.0 cm. The shaft rests on two rails with&nbsp;the cylinder able to spin freely between the rails.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/4753/Schermafbeelding_2018-08-12_om_16.44.54.png\" alt=\"M18/4/PHYSI/SP3/ENG/TZ2/06\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The stationary wheel is released from rest and rolls down a slope with the shaft rolling&nbsp;on the rails without slipping from point A to point B.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/4754/Schermafbeelding_2018-08-12_om_16.47.09.png\" alt=\"M18/4/PHYSI/SP3/ENG/TZ2/06.a\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Determine the angular velocity of the wheel at B.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em>ω</em>&nbsp;<strong>«</strong>= <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{1.2}}{{0.012}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1.2</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>0.012</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span><strong>»</strong> = 100&nbsp;<strong>«</strong>rad s<sup>–1</sup><strong>»</strong></p>\n<p><strong><em>[1 mark]</em><br></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"6029","referenceCode":"18M.3.SL.TZ2.6a.iii","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Determine the angular velocity of the wheel at B.","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a.iii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Option B: Engineering physics","Option B: Engineering physics","Option B: Engineering physics (Core topics)","B.1 – Rigid bodies and rotational dynamics","Option B: Engineering physics","Option B: Engineering physics (Core topics)"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}